\b\fs48 \cf0 Post via Email\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\b0\fs24 \cf0 You can post from an email client! To set this up go to your "Writing" options screen and fill in the connection details for your secret POP3 account. Then you need to set up 
\f1 wp-mail.php
\f0  to execute periodically to check the mailbox for new posts. You can do it with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cron"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 cron}}-jobs, or if your host doesn't support it you can look into the various website-monitoring services, and make them check your 
\f1 wp-mail.php
\f0  URL.\
Posting is easy: Any email sent to the address you specify will be posted, with the subject as the title. It is best to keep the address discrete. The script will 
\i delete
\i0  emails that are successfully posted.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320

